 
http://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/158289/finding-largest-file-recursively

use find to output file names with the file size. sort. print out the largest one.

find . -type f -printf "%s\t%p\n" | sort -n | tail -1

A "pure" bash solution

shopt -s globstar
max_s=0
for f in **; do
  if [[ -f "$f" ]]; then
    size=$( stat -c %s "$f" )
    if (( $size > $max_s )); then
      max_s=$size
      max_f=$f
    fi
  fi
done
echo "$max_s $max_f"